memberdef.name: ProcessOne

detaileddescription.para: Clicks are identified as small regions of high amplitude compared to the surrounding chunk of sound. Anything sufficiently tall compared to a large (2048 sample) window around it, and sufficiently narrow, is considered to be a click.
The structure was largely stolen from Domonic Mazzoni's NoiseRemoval module, and reworked for the NEW effect.
